  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2283",
  "title": "Allow faceting on non-scalar attributes (e.g. for refinementList)",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n*feature*\r\n\r\nI have an attribute like so:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n{\r\n  productCategories: {\r\n    title: 'Kayak',\r\n    value: 'kayak',\r\n    level: 1,\r\n  } \r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently, I have a `refinementList` widget, with the `attributeName` set to `productCategories.title`.\r\n\r\nWorks, but isn't quite what I want. I _want_ to set the `attributeName` to simply `productCategories`, and the be able to use all of those properties to render (and filter) the template.\r\n\r\nHere's my (non-working) attempt for configuring a `refinementList` widget:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n{\r\n      attributeName: 'productCategories',\r\n      templates: {\r\n        item: (data) => {\r\n          const template = Hogan.compile(defaultTemplates.item);\r\n\r\n          if (data.level > 1) {\r\n            return null;\r\n          }\r\n        \r\n          return template.render(data);\r\n        }\r\n      },\r\n\r\n      transformData: {\r\n        item: (data) => {\r\n          return Object.assign(data, {\r\n            label: data.value.title,\r\n            value: data.value.slug,\r\n          });\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n↑ I'm attempting to set the `attributeName` to `productCategories`, hoping that that would pass the whole object as `data.value` to `transformData.item`. I'm also attempting to filter out items based on some other data in that object in in `templates.item`.\r\n\r\nIt seems like I need another method/option to prep the data?\r\n\r\nRelated: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/739",
